      <title>Re: **HALFLING** PvP **HALFLING**?</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=PVP&amp;message.id=12299#M12299</link>
      <description>&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;It's been a common theme.&amp;nbsp; My experience, and that of Hangman, are pretty much like yours.&amp;nbsp; Not a lot you can do against high end melee right now.&amp;nbsp; I have pyro and splurt up in my PVP set too, which is just plain sad.&amp;nbsp; Blood of Thule will land for you sometimes if you debuff with Scent of Midnight (or whatever you have in the scent line) first.&amp;nbsp; Your duration taps also are less resist-challenged than your dots.&amp;nbsp; Try Night's Beckon or Fang of Death.&amp;nbsp; Forget your 70 spells, the checks on them are such that they will be resisted just about all the time by anyone with resists over 400.&amp;nbsp; Your tap isn't good for much against high-end players (it lands for too little to damage them for much, or heal you for much).&amp;nbsp; You can use it to tap a green mob for some HP if you're in a greenie zone, but that's about all.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;The lower&amp;nbsp;end spells&amp;nbsp;will do a decent amount of damage if you have good focus gear and aas because they'll tick for a long time.&amp;nbsp; Most of they players that you'll be PvPing against know that they can cure/dispell them though, so chances are that they won't.&amp;nbsp; You aren't going to be mana efficient enough to kill anyone with more HP than you have mana&amp;nbsp;unless the fight goes long and you regen mana faster than they regen HP (including hitting heal pots).&amp;nbsp; That isn't going to happen too often because playing cat-and-mouse doesn't usually work with the rampant use of 3rd party software that allows all classes to track.&amp;nbsp; Bottom line, you aren't going to beat a high-end melee by yourself right now.&amp;nbsp; Bout all you can do right now is always travel with a group until the tide turns again, which could happen if SOE gets their thumb ouf of their .... um.... ear and figures out how to test their software, instead of just guessing at what a reasonable resist check might be.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
